  "target_response": {
    "text": "Yes — slow dieting is exactly the right call, and your instinct to skip water loading and sauna cuts is a good one; the acute-dehydration route is where weight cutting becomes genuinely risky. Your maths is friendly: 1.5 kg across six weeks is about 0.25 kg per week, which a small daily calorie deficit handles comfortably. Keep protein high and training normal so the loss comes from fat rather than strength, aim to sit at 66 kg about a week before the competition, then eat and drink normally through comp week — no last-minute manipulation needed. Track the weekly average of morning weigh-ins rather than single days. Worth mentioning the plan to your club coach so they know you're arriving on-weight the sustainable way; for competition weight classes that bit of supervision is genuinely useful.",
